column5: Checking in from Cleveland where the Eye fishing has been great this year!  Latest trip was last Sunday. I went in out of Ashtabula (eastern Ohio) and by noon I had my limit, which included 4 at 9 lbs or greater.  Heading up to Nipissing the 1st week of August.  Hope to remember my camera this time!
Wow, 4 fish at least 9 lbs. I would say that was a decent day!!
Welcome aboard Bcee. Awesome job on the eyes. Have a great time on Nipissing.
love them eyes.....you will not get many that big on Nipissing but lots of good eater size welcome aboard
Great little report...good luck on Nipissing..just rememer there is a slot there now for Walleye.
Yeah, I know about the slot. Been fishing up there since I was a lil angler...not so lil anymore..LOL!!
Welcome to the board, lot of fun at Nipissing
Welcome to the board Bcee, have a great time at Nippissing and please don't forget the camera...we like Pictures  Maureen
Welcome bcee...hope you enjoy it here as much as the rest of us
welcome aboard and bring that camera so we can see some pic's of these pics
im also heading to nipissing for first week of august !

Lil Angler,  where ya staying?  We will be at Tall Pines on Sandy Island.  When I was a kid, my summers were spent on that island from mid july (when baseball ended) thru mid august.  Friends of my family would come up week after week and I would just hand and play and fish.  Glorious times...glorious!  BTW, that pic (avatar) is my daughter last year..she hooked into that bass in front of Sandy Haven Camp. It was her first fish (4 lbs)..she is hooked.  The pic was taken back at camp on one of those 1970's instamatic cameras that spit out the photo and you watch it develop.
